XML Shallow Parsing with Regular Expression: [^]]*]([^]]+])*]+.  The intent of [^]] is probably [^\]].  An unescaped ']' is not allowed in a character class, so the expression is parsed as [^] (empty inverted class) followed by a literal ']', which is a SyntaxError.  There are two other literal ']' issues.  The RegExp can be fixed to: /[^\]]*\]([^\]]+\])*\]+/.

diagnosed: Duktape bug, matching /(a*)b\1+/ against 'baaaac' causes first capture to match the empty string; the '\1+' part will then use the '+' quantifier over the empty string.  As there is no handling to empty quantified now, Duktape bails out with a RangeError.
